2C%20small%20single-family%20homes%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wanot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20tip%20is%20to%20look%20for%20property%20where%20the%20seller%20has%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%2050%25%20equity%20in%20the%20home%20and%20has%20owned%20it%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20as%20they%20might%20be%20more%20motivated%20to%20negotiate%2C%20especially%20if%20they're%20managing%20it%20from%20out-of-state.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20looking%20at%20owners%20who%20are%20over%20the%20age%20of%2050%20because%20the%20older%20owners%20tend%20to%20want%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20real%20estate%20space.%20It%20is%20so%20draining%20and%20requires%20a%20lot%20of%20physical%20and%20mental%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWanot%20owns%20multi-family%20properties%20but%20has%20found%20that%20they're%20more%20difficult%20to%20make%20the%20numbers%20work%2C%20at%20least%20in%20his%20current%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20a%20sophisticated%20investor%2C%20yes%2C%20small%20or%20large%20multi-families%20are%20good%20if%20you%20actually%20have%20run%20your%20numbers%201%2C000%20times%20and%20you%20know%20exactly%20what%20you're%20looking%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20probably%20five%20properties%20that%20I%20was%20going%20to%20buy%20in%20the%20last%20year%20that%20I%20didn't%20pull%20the%20trigger%20on%20because%20the%20profit%20and%20loss%20statements%20that%20were%20given%20to%20me%20were%20significantly%20different%20from%20the%20actual%20bank%20statements.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20mistake%20he's%20seen%20investors%20make%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20these%20big%20multi-families%2C%20is%20just%20paying%20attention%20to%20the%20P%26amp%3BLs%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20are%20made%20by%20the%20property%20managers%20or%20the%20owners%20of%20the%20property%20and%20show%20one%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20actually%20going%20through%20the%20bank%20statements%20and%20seeing%