rth-lesson-husband-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblindsiding%20breakup%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20my%20boyfriend%2C%20my%20mother%20began%20losing%20our%20home%20back%20on%20the%20East%20Coast.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20lost%20control%20of%20the%20wheel.%20The%20one%20thing%20in%20my%20life%20I%20could%20control%3F%20What%20I%20ate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Ffood-journal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20journal.%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20carried%20it%20everywhere%2C%20jotting%20down%20every%20single%20thing%20I%20put%20in%20my%20mouth.%20Even%20a%20couple%20of%20grapes%20or%20a%20small%20handful%20of%20granola%20had%20to%20be%20tracked%20and%20recorded.%20Then%20I%20began%20following%20several%20nutrition%20blogs%20and%20reading%20those%20oh-so-problematic%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20I%20eat%20in%20a%20day%26quot%3B%20posts.%20Now%20I%20know%20that%20those%20bloggers'%20meals%20didn't%20provide%20enough%20calories%20for%20me%2C%20but%20at%20the%20time%20they%20were%20something%20I%20looked%20to%20for%20inspiration.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20false%20sense%20of%20control%20I%20gained%20from%20tracking%20calories%20and%20counting%20almonds%20was%20intoxicating%20%E2%80%94%20and%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthy-eating-tips-food-routines-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehabits%3C%2Fa%3E%20gradually%20spiraled.%20Soon%20I%20had%20to%20measure%20every%20tablespoon%20of%20peanut%20butter%20I%20spread%20on%20a%20sandwich%20or%20the%20oil%20I%20drizzled%20on%20a%20salad.%20It%20became%20impossible%20to%20enjoy%20a%20meal%20out%20with%20friends%2C%20because%20I%20knew%20I'd%20lie%20awake%20later%20that%20night%20riddled%20with%20anxiety%20about%20not%20knowing%20exactly%20what%20I'd%20consumed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20funny.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20felt%20so%20in%20control%20when%20in%20reality%2C%20the%20disorder%20had%20begun%20controlling%20me.%20It%20had%20the%20final%20say%20on%20where%2C%20what%2C%20and%20how%20much%20I%20could%20eat%2C%20and%20the%20joy%20I%20could%20derive%20from%20enjoying%20food%20with%20loved%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20when%20the%20holidays%20rolled%20around%20that%20year%2C%20the%20emphasis%20on%20food%20no%20longer%20felt%20like%20a%20perk.%20Instead%2C%20it%20was%20agonizing.%20In%20the%20days%20leading%20up%20to%20Thanksgiving%2C%20I%20spent%20hours%20plotting%20how%20I%20could%20fool%20my%20family%20into%20thinking%20I'd%20feasted%20along%20with%20them%20while%20hiding%20food%20in%20a%20napkin.%20And%20then%20I%20spent%20countless%20sleepless%20nights%20after%20Christmas%20simultaneously%20shaming%20myself%20for%20my%20choices%20and%20wrestling%20with%20regret%20that%20I%20hadn't%20allowed%20myself%20to%20indulge%20in%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fupgrade-holiday-desserts-with-peppermint-bark-christina-tosi-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efavorite%20treats%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20young%20girl%20in%20a%20black%20top%20sits%20at%20a%20bar%20with%20a%20glass%20of%20wine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6757332052dd0818d1a5fb11%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20photo%20was%20taken%20in%20December%20of%202011%2C%20a%20month%20before%20I%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20an%20eating%20disorder.%20Before%20meeting%20my%20friend%20for%20drinks%2C%20I%20remember%20eating%20dinner%20at%20home%20because%20it%20felt%20%26quot%3Bsafer.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Strong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2267ce0aff-548b-4b51-8b73-580186dbd281%5C%22%3EA%20turning%20point%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20December%20marks%2013%20years%20since%20I%20hit%20rock%20bottom.%20And%20from%20this%20vantage%20point%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20believe%20that%20my%20eating%20disorder%20almost%20ruined%20all%20of%20my%20favorite%20holidays%20for%20me.%20Although%20my%20mom%20and%20other%20family%20members%20had%20urged%20me%20to%20get%20help%2C%20only%20I%20could%20make%20that%20decision%20for%20myself%20and%20put%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhad-every-eating-disorder-what-not-to-ask-people-struggling-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20it%20takes%20to%20recover%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20I%20realized%20that%20my%20eating%20disorder%20was%20impairing%20my%20social%20life%2C%20dating%20life%2C%20and%20ability%20to%20travel%20while%20also%20holding%20me%20back%20from%20achieving%20my%20career%20goals%20and%20sapping%20all%20the%20joy%20out%20of%20fun%20celebratory%20occasions%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20seek%20professional%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20extensive%20therapy%20for%20me%20to%20get%20here%20%E2%80%94%20to%20unpack%20the%20fears%20and%20feelings%20at%20the%20root%20of%20my%20disordered%20thoughts%20and%20habits%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20finally%20reached%20what%20I%20consider%20to%20be%20a%20full%20recovery%20from%20my%20eating%20disorder%20at%20age%2023.%20I%20feel%20so%20fortunate%20to%20have%20worked%20with%20Dr.%20Jennifer%20Thomas%2C%20a%20psychologist%20who%20has%20since%20become%20the%20co-director%20of%20the%20Eating%20Disorders%20Clinical%20and%20Research%20Program%20at%20Massachusetts%20General%20Hospital.%20During%20our%20weekly%20sessions%2C%20she%20gave%20me%20challenges%20to%20try%20at%20home%20that%20often%20felt%20uncomfortable%20%E2%80%94%20eating%20at%20different%20times%20than%20my%20usual%20schedule%2C%20incorporating%20%26quot%3Bfear%20foods%26quot%3B%20back%20into%20my%20routine%20one%20by%20one%2C%20and%20offered%20invaluable%20support%20as%20I%20dug%20into%20the%20desperation%20for%20control%20that%20was%20driving%20my%20eating%20disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20in%20a%20black%20top%20enjoys%20a%20meal%20out.%20A%20plate%20with%20salad%20is%20on%20the%20table%20and%20she%20is%20raising%20a%20glass%20to%20cheers%20with%20friends.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67573381dc8b666017f20ec3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222362%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHere%20I%20am%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202024%2C%20enjoying%20a%20meal%20out%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20would%20have%20been%20unthinkable%20pre-recovery.%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Strong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6a4ec57-f375-4c5b-971b-4f97bb6284d1%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3ENow%2C%20I%20make%20a%20choice%20to%20be%20healthy%20every%20day%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20I've%20given%20several%20speeches%20at%20my%20local%20chapter%20of%20the%20National%20Eating%20Disorders%20Association%20to%20offer%20hope%20for%20people%20on%20their%20own%20recovery%20journey.%20During%20these%20speeches%2C%20I've%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20give%20people%20a%20realistic%20idea%20of%20what%20life%20looks%20like%20post-recovery.%20In%20setting%20those%20expectations%2C%20I've%20told%20them%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20your%20disorder%20disappears.%20It's%20just%20so%20much%20easier%20to%20squash%20that%20toxic%20inner%20dialogue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMindfulness%20has%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20my%20recovery%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20way%20I%20cope%20at%20food-focused%20holidays%20and%20other%20occasions.%20For%20so%20many%20years%2C%20I%20ignored%20what%20my%20body%20was%20trying%20to%20tell%20me.%20It%20got%20to%20the%20point%20where%20I%20didn't%20even%20notice%20hunger%20cues%20or%20cravings%20anymore.%20Practicing%20mindfulness%20has%20helped%20me%20to%20tune%20back%20into%20those%20signals%20so%20that%20when%20disordered%20thoughts%20arise%2C%20I%20can%20check%20in%20internally%20and%20make%20decisions%20based%20on%20my%20body's%20%3Cem%3Eactual%20%3C%2Fem%3Eneeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20surveying%20the%20family-style%20feast%20on%20Thanksgiving%2C%20my%20mind%20is%20sometimes%20quick%20to%20whisper%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20should%20load%20up%20on%20carrots%20rather%20than%20mashed%20potatoes%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BYou%20already%20had%20sugar-laden%20cranberry%20sauce%2C%20you%20should%20skip%20the%20pie.%26quot%3B%20The%20difference%20now%20is%20that%20it's%20become%20easier%20to%20dismiss%20that%20voice%2C%20like%20an%20old%20frenemy%20whose%20advice%20and%20opinions%20I%20just%20don't%20value%20any%20longer.%20And%20every%20time%20I%20opt%20to%20pay%20no%20attention%20to%20it%2C%20it%20gets%20a%20little%20bit%20quieter.%20Nowadays%2C%20I%20often%20reach%20the%20end%20of%20a%20holiday%20celebration%20realizing%20that%20I%20didn't%20hear%20my%20eating%20disorder's%20unhelpful%20input%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ucsf.edu%2Fnews%2F2019%2F11%2F416006%2Fmany-patients-anorexia-nervosa-get-better-complete-recovery-elusive-most%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20only%20around%2021%25%20of%20people%20make%20a%20full%20recovery%20from%20an%20eating%20disorder.%20I'm%20very%20grateful%20to%20count%20myself%20among%20that%20minority%20because%20as%20the%20holidays%20fast%20approach%20again%20this%20year%2C%20I'm%20not%20worrying%20about%20how%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20through%26quot%3B%20while%20depriving%20myself%20of%20all%20the%20foods%20that%20bring%20me%20joy%20and%20pleasure.%20I'm%20far%20more%20focused%20on%20how%20grateful%20I%20am%20to%20even%20have%20access%20to%20these%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20something%20so%20many%20Americans%20lack.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EMy%20memories%20of%20those%20holidays%20during%20the%20peak%20of%20my%20disorder%20feel%20so%20hazy%2C%20like%20a%20photograph%20that's%20faded%20beyond%20perceptibility.%20This%20year%2C%20rather%20than%20being%20distracted%20by%20my%20own%20anxious%20thoughts%2C%20I'm%20focused%20on%20being%20present%20with%20my%20family%