20it%20works.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Happy%20family%20aboard%20a%20yacht%20out%20to%20sea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b7b6926c8f0a134f7aabbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20rich%20can%20use%20private-placement%20life%20insurance%20to%20save%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%3Cp%3EViewStock%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20richest%20of%20the%20rich%20can%20use%20life%20insurance%20to%20avoid%20estate%20and%20income%20taxes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPrivate-placement%20life%20insurance%20is%20perfectly%20legal%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20a%20new%20bill%20passes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20financial%20advisor%20tells%20Insider%20how%20the%20insurance%20saves%20the%20wealthy%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELife%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20probably%20the%20least%20sexy%20area%20of%20financial%20planning.%20But%20for%20the%20richest%20of%20the%20rich%2C%20policies%20can%20slash%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20off%20their%20tax%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate-placement%20life%20insurance%20is%20a%20little-known%20tax-avoidance%20tactic.%20When%20structured%20correctly%2C%20PPLI%20policies%20can%20be%20used%20to%20pass%20on%20assets%20from%20stocks%20to%20yachts%20to%20heirs%20without%20incurring%20an%20estate%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20US%2C%20people%20sell%20life%20insurance%20as%20a%20middle-class%20way%20of%20structuring%20assets%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Malloy%2C%20a%20wealth%20advisor%20who%20has%20specialized%20in%20PPLI%20for%2020%20years%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%202022.%20%26quot%3BBut%20PPLI%20is%20a%20completely%20different%20animal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PPLI%20industry%20enables%20a%20few%20thousand%20ultra-rich%20American%20taxpayers%20to%20shelter%20at%20least%20%2440%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20an%20investigation%20by%20the%20Senate%20Finance%20Committee.%20The%20report%20estimated%20that%20the%20average%20PPLI%20policyholder%20is%20worth%20well%20over%20%24100%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPPLI%20is%20legal%E2%80%94for%20now.%20On%20December%2016%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fron-wyden-billionaire-profile-biography-tax-biden-economic-agenda-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOregon%20Sen.%20Ron%20Wyden%20%3C%2Fa%3Ereleased%20a%20draft%20bill%20to%20close%20the%20loophole.%20Under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.finance.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fppli_abuse_act_discussion_draft_one-pagerpdf.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProtecting%20Proper%20Life%20Insurance%20from%20Abuse%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20PPLI%20policies%20would%20be%20treated%20as%20investment%20funds%2C%20not%20life%20insurance%20or%20annuity%20policies%2C%20which%20would%20eliminate%20the%20tax%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLife%20insurance%20is%20an%20essential%20source%20of%20financial%20security%20for%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20middle-class%20families%20in%20America%2C%20so%20we%20cannot%20have%20a%20bunch%20of%20ultra-rich%20tax%20dodgers%20abusing%20its%20special%20tax%20treatment%20to%20set%20up%20tax-free%20hedge%20funds%20and%20shelter%20oodles%20of%20cash%2C%26quot%3B%20Wyden%20said%20in%20a%20written%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20tax%20savings%20are%20the%20primary%20draw%20of%20PPLI%20for%20US%20clients%2C%20those%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20or%20Latin%20America%20are%20often%20looking%20to%20use%20trusts%20to%20conceal%20information%20about%20specific%20assets%20from%20corrupt%20governments%2C%20Malloy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClients%20don't%20want%20an%20organized%20crime%20ring%20bribing%20an%20underpaid%20tax%20official%20to%20get%20information%20on%20their%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20taxpayers%20are%20required%20to%20report%20to%20the%20IRS%20only%20the%20cash%20value%20of%20a%20foreign%20life-insurance%20policy%2C%20not%20the%20assets%20within%20the%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20offshore%20life%20insurers%20in%20jurisdictions%20such%20as%20the%20Cayman%20Islands%20and%20Bermuda%20typically%20require%20at%20least%20%245%20million%20as%20the%20upfront%20premium.%20Malloy%20advises%20that%20clients%20have%20at%20least%20%2410%20million%20in%20assets%20to%20make%20PPLI%20worthwhile.%20His%20clients%20usually%20hold%20at%20least%20%2450%20million%20in%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287f2ccc9-51b5-4ffe-a0dc-304ce8bf33d4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere%20is%20how%20PPLI%20works%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20an%20attorney%20sets%20up%20a%20trust%20for%20a%20wealthy%20client.%20The%20trust%20owns%20the%20life-insurance%20policy%20that's%20created%20offshore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PPLI%20policy%20premiums%20are%20funded%20with%20assets.%20The%20assets%20must%20be%20diversified%20%E2%80%94%20typically%20with%20at%20least%20five%20different%20asset%20classes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20can%20include%20stocks%20and%20business%20interests%2C%20as%20well%20as%20tangible%20assets%20like%20yachts%20and%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20the%20client's%20age%2C%20nationality%2C%20and%20other%20factors%2C%20the%20death%20benefit%20can%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20max%20out%20at%20%24100%20million%2C%20Malloy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20structured%20correctly%2C%20the%20benefit%20and%20the%20assets%20in%20the%20policy%20are%20passed%20to%20the%20children%20without%20incurring%20an%20estate%20tax.%20A%2040%25%20federal%20estate%20tax%20applies%20to%20estate%20values%20topping%20%2413.61%20million%20for%20individuals%20and%20%2427.22%20million%20for%20married%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20with%20policies%20from%20US%20insurers%2C%20clients%20can%20cancel%20their%20policies%20without%20paying%20a%20massive%20surrender%20fee.%20The%20assets%20also%20grow%20within%20the%20trust%20tax-free.%20The%20cash%20value%20of%20the%20PPLI%20policy%20assets%20is%20held%20in%20a%20separate%20account%2C%20and%20this%20cash%20can%20be%20disbursed%20to%20the%20policy%20holder%20or%20invested.%20Investing%20in%20hedge%20funds%20is%20a%20popular%20use%20of%20PPLI%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20a%20catch.%20Policyholders%20have%20limited%20control%20over%20investment%20decisions.%20They%20cannot%20give%20directives%20to%20the%20asset%20manager%20to%20buy%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20shares%20in%20Apple%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20requires%20a%20small%20army%20of%20professionals%2C%20including%20trust%20and%20estate%20attorneys%2C%20asset%20managers%2C%20custodians%2C%20and%20tax%20advisors.%20Since%20PPLI%20is%20relevant%20only%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-rich-americans-avoid-estate-tax-on-real-estate-assets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultrawealthy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20few%20in%20wealth%20management%20or%20law%20are%20familiar%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20questions%20on%20the%20CPA%20exam%20or%20the%20bar%20exam%20about%20PPLI%2C%20and%20asset%20managers%20are%20kind%20of%20skeptical%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20think%20you're%20going%20to%20take%20assets%20away.%20Actually%2C%20the%20assets%20become%20stickier%20and%20get%20more%20alpha%20because%20the%20client%20pays%20less%20tax.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22414a618d-b466-4564-a577-79f779b18705%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20the%20proposed%20bill%20would%20endanger%20PPLI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Wyden's%20proposed%20legislation%2C%20most%20PPLI%20policies%20would%20be%20classified%20as%20%26quot%3Bprivate%20placement%20contracts%26quot%3B%20(PPCs)%20rather%20than%20life%20insurance%20policies.%20As%20such%2C%20any%20accumulated%20earnings%20and%20death%20benefits%20would%20be%20taxed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20would%20apply%20to%20future%20%3Cem%3Eand%20%3C%2Fem%3Eexisting%20PPLI%20policies%2C%20giving%20policyholders%20180%20days%20to%20liquify%20the%20assets%20or%20transfer%20them.%20Insurers%20who%20dare%20to%20issue%20or%20reinsure%20the%20policies%20will%20no%20longer%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20secrecy.%20To%20better%20enable%20the%20IRS%20to%20enforce%20the%20bill%2C%20insurers%20will%20have%20to%20report%20all%20PPCs%20or%20face%20a%20%241%20million%20fine%20for%20each%2030-day%20period%20that%20they%20fail%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20faces%20steep%20odds%20of%20passing%20with%20Donald%20Trump's%20reelection%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frepublicans-house-representatives-election-win-majority-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublican%20House%20and%20Senate%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20insurance%20industry%20is%20counting%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20legislation%20is%20an%20attack%20on%20all%20forms%20of%20permanent%20life%20insurance%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20an%20attack%20on%20holistic%20financial%20planning%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Marc%20Cadin%2C%20CEO%20of%20trade%20group%20Finseca%2C%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BWe%20look%20forward%20to%20working%20with%20the%20new%20Congress%20and%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20advance%20policies%20to%20move%20our%20country%20forward%20rather%20than%20raising%20taxes%20on%20life%20insurance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-placement-life-insurance-tax-shelter-ron-wyden-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734689101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F676334655cddac6581d6cd8d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-placement-life-insurance-tax-sh