20were%20not%20nailing%20basic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftricks-get-kids-interested-reading-books-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereading%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20third%20grade%20%E2%80%94%20a%20crucial%20window.%20Those%20who%20miss%20it%20have%20a%20tough%20road%20ahead%20in%20middle%20and%20high%20school.%20Even%20adept%20readers%20in%20their%20tweens%20and%20teens%20have%20become%20afraid%20of%20complex%20or%20extended%20reading%20tasks%20and%20more%20comfortable%20with%20short%20texts%20or%20bite-size%20summaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcGoun%2C%20who%20has%20a%20doctorate%20in%20education%2C%20shared%20one%20stark%20example.%20With%20struggling%20readers%2C%20he%20hands%20each%20child%20a%20book%20upside%20down%20and%20backward.%20%26quot%3BThey%20should%20be%20able%20to%20turn%20the%20book%20the%20right%20way%20up%20and%20open%20it%20at%20the%20first%20page%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20These%20days%2C%20%26quot%3Bsome%20students%20aren't%20able%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20unusual.%20Across%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudents-math-and-reading-scores-drop-drastically-during-the-pandemic-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekids%20are%20struggling%20to%20read%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20year%2C%20reading%20performance%20for%20fourth%20graders%20hit%20its%20lowest%20level%20since%202005%2C%20and%20teachers%20expect%20that%20number%20to%20keep%20tumbling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20panic%20to%20turn%20things%20around%20quickly%20is%20driving%20a%20wedge%20between%20teachers%2C%20politicians%2C%20and%20parents%2C%20all%20pointing%20the%20finger%20of%20blame%20at%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Senate%20education%20committee%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20crisis%2C%20is%20pushing%20school%20districts%20to%20retrain%20teachers%20in%20a%20trendy%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finternational-baccalaureate-enrolled-american-program-uk-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteaching%20style%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20%26quot%3Bthe%20science%20of%20reading%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20has%20dramatically%20improved%20literacy%20in%20some%20areas%20(scroll%20down%20for%20more%20detail%20on%20that).%20Parents%20with%20resources%20to%20do%20so%20are%20moving%20their%20kids%20to%20schools%20that%20tout%20science-backed%20teaching%20styles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20teachers%20and%20policy%20experts%20worry%20this%20frenzy%20may%20have%20an%20ironic%20side%20effect%2C%20putting%20pressure%20on%20public%20schools%20to%20resolve%20a%20problem%20that%20cannot%20be%20tackled%20in%20the%20classroom%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20the%20task%20of%20teaching%20harder%2C%26quot%3B%20McGoun%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20new%20literacy%20programs%20and%20a%20focus%20on%20test%20results.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20burning%20out%20at%20a%20faster%20rate%2C%20and%20it's%20causing%20a%20lot%20of%20apathy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Alpha%20kids%2C%20aged%202%20to%2012%2C%20need%20to%20discover%20the%20joy%20of%20reading%2C%20he%20and%20other%20teachers%20say.%20It's%20doable%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20more%20creative%20and%20slower%20process%20that%20many%20parents%20don't%20have%20time%20to%20wait%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22edb0aa34-dc23-4b2e-8502-877e64625dc3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETeaching%20a%206-year-old%20to%20read%20is%20political%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20never%20been%20a%20golden%20age%20for%20reading%20scores%20in%20America.%20The%20record%20high%20was%20in%202017%2C%20when%2037%25%20of%20US%20fourth%20graders%20pass%20their%20NAEP%20reading%20test%20%E2%80%94%20just%205%25%20higher%20than%20the%20most%20recent%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20this%20new%20low%20raised%20alarm%20among%20lawmakers%20who%20were%20already%20concerned%20about%20screens%20and%20loneliness%20among%20Gen%20Alpha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20long-term%20implications%20will%20be%20dire%E2%80%9D%20if%20literacy%20does%20not%20improve%2C%20Sen.%20Bill%20Cassidy%2C%20the%20top%20Republican%20on%20the%20Senate%20education%20committee%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.help.senate.gov%2Franking%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress%2Franking-member-cassidy-releases-troubling-report-on-child-literacy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20February%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20having%20an%20entire%20generation%20of%20children%2C%20those%20who%20were%20in%20their%20prime%20learning%20years%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20fail%20to%20become%20productive%20adults%20if%20reading%20proficiency%20does%20not%20improve.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20proposed%20solution%3F%20Get%20all%20teachers%20to%20use%20the%20same%2C%20evidence-backed%20teaching%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeaching%20styles%20have%20served%20as%20political%20footballs%20for%20over%20100%20years.%20The%20fierce%2C%20ongoing%20debate%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.harvard.edu%2Ffiles%2Fjameskim%2Ffiles%2Fbookch2.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereading%20wars%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20dates%20back%20to%20at%20least%20the%20mid-19th%20century%2C%20when%20Horace%20Mann%2C%20then%20Massachusetts%E2%80%99%20education%20secretary%2C%20slammed%20the%20alphabet%20as%20%E2%80%9Cskeleton-shaped%2C%20bloodless%2C%20ghostly%20apparitions%E2%80%9D%20and%20said%20children%20should%20be%20taught%20whole%20words%20rather%20than%20their%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20teaching%20unions%20maintain%20that%20teachers%20should%20be%20able%20to%20draw%20from%20various%20teaching%20styles%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20tough%20sell%20with%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CParents%20and%20others%20are%20getting%20upset%20about%20their%20kids%E2%80%99%20literacy%20curriculum%20because%20they've%20heard%20that%20there's%20a%20certain%20way%20to%20teach%20kids%20how%20to%20read%2C%20and%20that%20might%20not%20be%20properly%20implemented%20in%20schools%2C%E2%80%9D%20Carly%20Robinson%2C%20a%20senior%20education%20researcher%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cscience%20of%20reading%E2%80%9D%20method%20(see%20chart%20below)%20has%20been%20touted%20as%20a%20silver%20bullet%20that%20transformed%20literacy%20rates%20in%20Mississippi%20between%202013%20and%202019%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20areas%20with%20high%20child-poverty%20rates%2C%20which%20typically%20correlate%20with%20lower%20literacy%20levels.%20It%20became%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chalkbeat.org%2F2023%2F7%2F18%2F23799124%2Fmississippi-miracle-test-scores-naep-early-literacy-grade-retention-reading-phonics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMississippi%20Miracle%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20February%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.help.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fliteracy_report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Senate%20education%20committee%20said%20teachers%20who%20still%20used%20other%20methods%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20the%20three-cueing%20system%20%E2%80%94%20were%20setting%20students%20%E2%80%9Cup%20for%20failure%20in%20the%20long%20run.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225120ed31-55f1-4cea-8614-3349e083fe9f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETEACHING%20STYLES%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Ctable%3E%3Ccolgroup%3E%3Ccol%3E%3Ccol%3E%3Ccol%3E%3Ccol%3E%3C%2Fcolgroup%3E%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%3EStyle%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhole%20language%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EThree-cueing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EScience%20of%20reading%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EHow%20it%20works%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EPopular%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20%E2%80%9990s%2C%20this%20style%20is%20about%20learning%20words%20through%20immersion.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EA%20teacher%20practicing%20this%20approach%20repeatedly%20shows%20students%20a%20set%20of%20words%2C%20using%20photos%20to%20help%20them%20remember%20the%20meanings.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ECritics%20said%20the%20whole-language%20approach%20made%20students%20rely%20on%20context%20instead%20of%20learning%20to%20sound%20out%20unfamiliar%20words.%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EPopularized%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20this%20model%20blends%20contextual%2C%20visual%2C%20and%20grammar%20techniques.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EKids%20are%20given%20three%20cues%3A%20semantic%20(the%20meaning%20of%20the%20word)%2C%20syntactic%20(how%20the%20word%20is%20used%20in%20a%20sentence)%2C%20and%20graphophonic%20(letters%20and%20sounds).%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ECritics%20of%20three-cueing%20say%20it%20could%20teach%20students%20to%20interpret%20words%20incorrectly.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20student%20could%20look%20at%20a%20photo%20of%20a%20horse%20and%20read%20%26quot%3Bpony.%26quot%3B%20They%20might%20not%20be%20corrected%20because%20the%20meaning%20makes%20sense%20within%20the%20context%20of%20the%20sentence%20and%20the%20photo.%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Cscience%20of%20reading%E2%80%9D%20places%20emphasis%20on%20decoding%20words.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIt%20is%20rooted%20in%20an%20approach%20developed%20in%20the%201930s%20by%20the%20neuropsychiatrist%20Samuel%20Orton%20and%20the%20psychologist%20Anna%20Gillingham.%20Take%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cchip.%26quot%3B%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EInstructors%20focus%20on%20teaching%20students%20to%20identify%20the%20individual%20sounds%20each%20letter%20makes%20alone%20and%20those%20they%20make%20when%20combined%20%E2%80%94%20like%20%E2%80%9Cch%E2%80%9D%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%9Cc%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ch%E2%80%9D%20individually.%20Given%20the%20word%20chip's%20multiple%20meanings%2C%20you%20may%20be%20able%20to%20identify%20the%20major%20challenge%20with%20methods%20that%20focus%20on%20flashcards%20or%20context%20clues.%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3Ctr%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EWhere%20it's%20used%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EThese%20days%2C%20elements%20of%20the%20whole-language%20method%20are%20used%2C%20particularly%20in%20Montessori%20and%20Waldorf%20schools%2C%20but%20it%20is%20no%20longer%20popular%20as%20a%20singular%20method.%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EAt%20least%20eight%20states%2C%20including%20Florida%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Wisconsin%2C%20banned%20three-cueing%20last%20year%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20science-of-reading%20method.%3C%2Ftd%3E%3Ctd%20colspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20rowspan%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3EA%20growing%20number%20of%20states%20across%20the%20country%20are%20adopting%20the%20science-of-reading%20methods.%3C%2Ftd%3E%3C%2Ftr%3E%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20states%2C%20parents%20want%20a%20Mississippi%20Miracle%20of%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESusie%20Coughlin%2C%20a%20mom%20in%20Falmouth%2C%20Maine%2C%20found%20herself%20going%20down%20rabbit%20holes%20about%20literacy%20techniques%20after%20her%205-year-old%20daughter%2C%20Carter%2C%20repeated%20kindergarten.%20Despite%20spending%20a%20second%20year%20at%20that%20level%2C%20the%20little%20girl%20had%20fallen%20behind%20in%20reading%20and%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20near%20the%20end%20of%20the%20school%20year%2C%20Coughlin%20saw%20a%20piece%20of%20Carter%E2%80%99s%20homework%20where%20she%20had%20written%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20went%20to%20the%20osen%2C%E2%80%9D%20rather%20than%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20went%20to%20the%20ocean.%E2%80%9D%20The%20teacher%20had%20not%20corrected%20the%20mistake%20because%20the%20emphasis%20was%20on%20visual%20cues%20%E2%80%94%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20sea%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20spelling.%20Coughlin%20was%20appalled%3B%20spelling%20was%20why%20Carter%20struggled%20to%20keep%20up%20in%20other%20classes.%20The%20mom%20took%20up%20her%20concerns%20with%20the%20teacher%2C%20who%2C%20she%20said%2C%20defended%20the%20visual%20method.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoughlin%20said%20that%20the%20impression%20the%20teacher%20gave%20off%20was%20that%20the%20school%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20going%20to%20let%20your%20child%20slide%20through.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BSo%20we%20hit%20the%20brakes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarter%20finished%20the%20year%2C%20but%20her%20parents%20elected%20to%20send%20her%20to%20a%20private%20Catholic%20school%20for%20first%20grade.%20In%20her%20new%20school%2C%20Carter%20was%20taught%20to%20%E2%80%9Csound%20it%20out%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20articulating%20the%20word%20as%20she%20read%20it%20rather%20than%20scanning%20pages%20for%20context%20cues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20progress%20was%20dramatic%2C%20Coughlin%20said.%20Now%208%20years%20old%2C%20Carter%20thrives%20in%20her%20second-grade%20reading%20classes.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20broke%20my%20heart%20when%20her%20confidence%20was%20in%20the%20toilet%20at%20her%20old%20school%2C%20but%20her%20bucket%20of%20self-esteem%20is%20filling%20up%2C%E2%80%9D%20Coughlin%2C%20who%20has%20since%20enrolled%20Carter%E2%80%99s%20younger%20brother%20at%20the%20same%20school%2C%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoughlin%20said%20her%20family%20was%20fortunate%20to%20have%20the%20resources%20to%20go%20private%20because%20the%20annual%20fees%20at%20the%20Catholic%20school%20are%20relatively%20low%3A%20%2410%2C000%20a%20child%2C%20compared%20with%20about%20%2440%2C000%20for%20secular%20private%20schools%20in%20Falmouth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForty-five%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20are%20considering%20bills%20that%20would%20retrain%20public%20school%20teachers%20in%20new%2C%20evidence-based%20reading%20practices.%20Susan%20Neuman%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20childhood%20and%20literacy%20education%20at%20New%20York%20University%20and%20an%20education%20official%20under%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%2C%20said%20the%20bills%20represented%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20biggest%2C%20boldest%2C%20and%20most%20inclusive%20effort%20to%20date%20to%20promote%20high-quality%2C%20scientifically%20supported%20reading%20instruction%20for%20all%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20fail.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEducators%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.the74million.org%2Farticle%2Fohio-science-of-reading-teachers-oppose-dewine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20so%20bullish%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20another%20initiative%20that%20requires%20retraining%20and%20devotion%20to%20new%20materials%20that%20cost%20hundreds%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eor%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20a%20year%2C%20preventing%20creativity%20with%20the%20syllabus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20problem%20is%20that%20some%20school%20districts%20think%3A%20%E2%80%98We%20pay%20for%20this%20program%2C%20and%20therefore%20you%20have%20to%20use%20this%20program.%E2%80%99%20You%20can't%20use%20anything%20else%2C%E2%80%9D%20McGoun%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20his%20school%20allows%20for%20flexibility%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20seen%20panic%20take%20over%20in%20other%20districts%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20teacher%2C%20you%20can't%20even%20make%20your%20own%20materials.%20It%E2%80%99s%20because%20the%20school%20district%20attended%20a%20conference%20and%20learned%20about%20a%20particular%20program%20%E2%80%94%20they%20promised%20XYZ%20outcomes%20if%20you%20only%20use%20its%20resources.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENailing%20the%20right%20method%20is%20not%20a%20teacher%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20concern%2C%20McGoun%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20important%20thing%20an%20educator%20can%20do%20is%20provide%20good%20pedagogy%20by%20focusing%20on%20the%20student%E2%80%99s%20interests%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20have%20motivated%20students%2C%20they%20will%20read.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9c9d04b-c869-404e-9294-058e3f9df4b6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKids%20are%20falling%20out%20of%20love%20with%20the%20written%20word%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%2C%20McGoun%20said%2C%20have%20%E2%80%9Cfallen%20out%20of%20love%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20written%20word%20because%20the%20march%20of%20technology%20has%20made%20it%20seem%20%E2%80%9Calien%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Coutmoded%E2%80%9D%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParents%20know%20tearing%20a%20school-age%20child%20away%20from%20a%20phone%20is%20no%20easy%20feat.%20No%20matter%20what%20literacy%20technique%20you%20employ%2C%20the%20pull%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkid-wants-smartphone-not-ready-decision-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreens%3C%2Fa%3E%20tends%20to%20be%20stronger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20efforts%20to%20leverage%20technology%20to%20help%20with%20literacy.%20Some%20artificial-intelligence%20programs%2C%20already%20appearing%20in%20classrooms%2C%20listen%20to%20students%20read%20aloud%20and%20give%20them%20instant%20feedback%20on%20pronunciation%20and%20comprehension%2C%20an%20alternative%20to%20having%20students%20play%20a%20reading%20game%20for%2010%20minutes%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubtitles%20on%20TV%20shows%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworldliteracyfoundation.org%2Fturn-on-the-subtitles%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DImproving%2520Reading%2520Comprehension%2520Subtitles%2520can%2Cformed%2520and%2520structured%2520within%2520sentences.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproved%20beneficial%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20early%20readers%20by%20presenting%20words%20on%20a%20screen%20that%20a%20child%20will%20read%2C%20sometimes%20without%20even%20realizing%20it%20%E2%80%94%20so%20much%20so%20that%20the%20actor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Do1xBvEhF5B0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJack%20Black%3C%2Fa%3E%20joined%20a%20campaign%20to%20promote%20subtitles%20to%20boost%20kids%E2%80%99%20literacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETara%20West%2C%20a%20former%20kindergarten%20teacher%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20literary-coaching%20organization%20Little%20Minds%20at%20Work%2C%20believes%20the%20benefits%20of%20constructive%20tech%20could%20outweigh%20the%20harm%20of%20kids%20spending%20too%20much%20time%20on%20screens.%20%E2%80%9CKids%20gravitate%20toward%20anything%20that%E2%80%99s%20digital%2C%E2%80%9D%20so%20teachers%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20that%2C%20West%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%E2%80%9CTechnology%20is%20going%20to%20go%20far.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20teachers%20on%20board%20may%20not%20be%20easy.%20In%20a%20recent%20Pew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2024%2F05%2F15%2Fa-quarter-of-u-s-teachers-say-ai-tools-do-more-harm-than-good-in-k-12-education%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20elementary-school%20teachers%2C%2047%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20sure%20how%20AI%20in%20classrooms%20would%20influence%20their%20students%E2%80%99%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Jarvis%2C%20a%20public-school%20teacher%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20is%20skeptical%20about%20the%20tech%20method.%20Sure%2C%20it%20might%20work%20in%20small%20groups%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20you%E2%80%99d%20almost%20definitely%20be%20struggling%20to%20use%20it%20effectively%20in%20a%20large%20class%20with%2025%20kids%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEducational%20digital%20media%20is%20%E2%80%9Coften%20attached%20to%20visuals%2C%20not%20texts%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jarvis%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99re%20getting%20quick%20blurbs%20from%20Snapchat%20and%20TikTok%20but%20nothing%20in-depth.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224107%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20teacher%20in%20a%20library%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675c6de6cf8d1359a2dfe60a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETeacher%20Jeff%20Jarvis%20would%20like%20parents%20to%20set%20an%20example%20for%20their%20kids%20by%20putting%20aside%20their%20phones%20and%20devoting%20more%20time%20to%20traditional%20reading.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Welsh%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETeachers%20like%20Jarvis%20and%20McGoun%20say%20that%2C%20at%20the%20most%20basic%20level%2C%20kids%20should%20be%20surrounded%20by%20books%20to%20simply%20learn%20how%20they%20work%20%E2%80%94%20turning%20physical%20pages%20instead%20of%20swiping%20on%20an%20iPad%2C%20for%20example.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20parents%20come%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPavel%20Buyeu%2C%20a%2043-year-old%20dad%20from%20Seattle%2C%20said%20that%20when%20his%20daughter%2C%20Liza%2C%20now%2015%2C%20began%20to%20show%20a%20reluctance%20to%20read%2C%20he%20feared%20she%E2%80%99d%20miss%20out%20on%20the%20joy%20and%20satisfaction%20of%20discovering%20books%20as%20a%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLiza%20and%20I%20are%20from%20different%20generations%20with%20different%20interests%2C%E2%80%9D%20Buyeu%20said.%20Still%2C%20he%20said%20he%20would%20like%20to%20see%20her%20enjoy%20some%20of%20the%20books%20he%20loved%20when%20he%20was%20younger.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20favorites%20were%20%E2%80%98The%20Adventures%20of%20Tom%20Sawyer%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98The%20Adventures%20of%20Huckleberry%20Finn%2C%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98The%20Little%20Prince%2C%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuyeu%20devised%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgame%E2%80%9D%20to%20make%20reading%20fun%20for%20Liza.%20He%E2%80%99d%20take%20his%20daughter%20to%20the%20bookstore%20and%20have%20her%20pick%20a%20title%20in%20return%20for%20privileges%20like%20sleeping%20in%20on%20weekends.%20The%20pair%20read%20and%20discussed%20the%20books%20before%20writing%20an%20alternative%20ending%20to%20the%20plot.%20Family%20members%20voted%20on%20a%20winner%2C%20which%20motivated%20Liza%20even%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CReading%20became%20a%20joy%20for%20her%2C%E2%80%9D%20Buyeu%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Liza%E2%80%99s%20reading%20speed%20and%20spelling%20improved%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuyeu%E2%80%99s%20game%20speaks%20to%20the%20power%20of%20parental%20involvement%20%E2%80%94%20a%20luxury%20not%20afforded%20to%20every%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2261807a46-a8df-47ef-8a24-f97df5f7ec76%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EParents%20with%20means%20are%20paying%20for%20tutoring%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELearning%20to%20read%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20about%20getting%20a%20grade%3B%20it%20can%20reverberate%20throughout%20someone%E2%80%99s%20career%20and%20personal%20life.%20Want%20to%20vote%3F%20It%20helps%20to%20be%20able%20to%20read%20and%20comprehend%20complex%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20not%20all%20students%20become%20readers%20in%20school%2C%20you%20will%20start%20to%20see%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20haves%20and%20the%20have-nots%2C%E2%80%9D%20Neuman%2C%20the%20former%20education%20official%2C%20said%20%E2%80%94%20people%20with%20the%20money%20to%20pay%20for%20extra%20help%20moving%20ahead%20in%20school%20and%20life%2C%20and%20those%20relying%20on%20public%20resources%20falling%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKumon%2C%20a%20private%20company%20that%20provides%20after-school%20math%20and%20reading%20tutoring%2C%20has%20recorded%20a%20recent%20surge%20in%20its%20number%20of%20new%20students%2C%20with%20enrollment%20increasing%20by%2056%25%20between%202020%20and%202024.%20The%20company%E2%80%99s%20methodology%20incorporates%20both%20meaning-based%20instruction%20and%20phonics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKalisha%20Brooks%20of%20Indian%20Land%2C%20South%20Carolina%2C%20enrolled%20her%20son%2C%20Corey%2C%20at%20Kumon%20when%20he%20was%20in%20kindergarten%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20She%20was%20worried%20that%20the%20disruption%20of%20the%20health%20crisis%20might%20set%20him%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99d%20read%20articles%20about%20children%20being%20home%20and%20getting%20further%20and%20further%20behind%2C%E2%80%9D%20Brooks%20said.%20So%20she%20bit%20the%20bullet%2C%20budgeting%20an%20extra%20%24200%20a%20month%20for%20Corey%20to%20have%20twice-weekly%20reading%20classes.%20She%E2%80%99s%20glad%20she%20did.%20Corey%2C%20now%208%2C%20performed%20above%20average%20in%20second%20grade%20and%20is%20now%20in%20third%20with%20a%20renewed%20confidence%20in%20reading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJessica%20Mercedes%20Penzari%2C%20a%2040-year-old%20mom%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20can%20relate%20to%20Brooks%E2%80%99%20dilemma.%20Her%20son%20Hendrix's%20kindergarten%20report%20card%20showed%20that%20he%20had%20dramatically%20fallen%20behind%20in%20reading%20within%20months.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20moment%20of%20panic%2C%E2%80%9D%20Penzari%20said.%20%E2%80%9COnce%20you%20fall%20behind%2C%20getting%20caught%20up%20is%20so%20difficult.%20I%20thought%2C%20%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99m%20slipping%20as%20a%20mom%20because%20my%20eye%20isn%E2%80%99t%20on%20the%20ball.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mother%20reading%20a%20book%20with%20her%20son.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675c6d9a52dd0818d1a71484%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221363%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJessica%20Mercedes%20Penzari%20and%20her%20son%2C%20Hendrix.%3Cp%3EMomo%20Takahashi%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPenzari%20secured%20a%20private%20tutor%20%E2%80%94%20a%20special-education%20teacher%20who%20lived%20in%20her%20building.%20She%20babysat%20the%20woman%E2%80%99s%20kids%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20typically%20%2475-an-hour%20lessons.%20It%20proved%20successful.%20Hendrix%2C%20who%20recently%20entered%20second%20grade%2C%20is%20back%20at%20proficiency%20level%20and%20above%20grade%20level%20in%20some%20subcategories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChildren%20who%20have%20fewer%20educational%20resources%20find%20themselves%20a%20step%20behind%20their%20peers%20at%20the%20outset.%20Just%2010%25%20of%20multilingual%20students%20can%20read%20proficiently%20by%20fourth%20grade%20compared%20with%2033%25%20of%20fourth%20graders%20overall%2C%20the%20NAEP%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Nichelle%20Watkins%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20public%20housing%20in%20Baltimore%2C%20told%20Fox%2045%20News%20that%20her%20fourth-grade%20son%2C%20Logan%2C%20still%20could%20not%20read%20and%20that%20they%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20afford%20tutoring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHow%20is%20he%20supposed%20to%20be%20productive%20if%20he%20can%E2%80%99t%20read%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20in%20the%20news%20segment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20go%20there%20to%20be%20babysat%20for%20eight%20hours%20and%20come%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20mom%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20Logan%E2%80%99s%20elementary%20school.%20She%20said%20legislators%20%E2%80%94%20to%20whom%20she%20later%20wrote%20pleading%20for%20improvements%20%E2%80%94%20ignored%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20feel%20like%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20care.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20their%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228f5f39e9-f0ac-4d0f-813f-e8ae16bb1e66%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225502%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Linda%20McMahon%20speaking%20at%20the%20Republican%20National%20Convention%20in%20Milwaukee.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673d4e6bede4eeae39288a13%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20WWE%20CEO%20Linda%20McMahon%2C%20Donald%20Trump's%20presumptive%20education%20secretary.%3Cp%3EBill%20Clark%2FCQ-Roll%20Call%2C%20Inc%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELinda%20McMahon%2C%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20pick%20to%20lead%20his%20Education%20Department%2C%20will%20have%20a%20mammoth%20managerial%20job%20on%20her%20hands%20if%20she%20is%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcMahon%2C%20a%20former%20wrestling%20executive%20who%20sat%20on%20the%20Board%20of%20Trustees%20for%20Sacred%20Heart%20University%20and%20served%20one%20year%20on%20Connecticut%E2%80%99s%20Board%20of%20Education%2C%20supports%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20deliver%20funds%20for%20education%20directly%20to%20states%2C%20giving%20them%20the%20authority%20to%20choose%20how%20to%20spend%20the%20money.%20She%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nea.org%2Fnea-today%2Fall-news-articles%2Ftop-three-reasons-linda-mcmahon-should-not-be-secretary-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esparked%20anger%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20some%20educators%20who%20argue%20her%20plans%20would%20hurt%20public%20schools.%20She%20has%20also%20been%20accused%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F11%2F21%2Fbusiness%2Flinda-mcmahon-abuse-wwe-trump-education%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20enabling%20sexual%20abuse%20of%20kids%20in%20the%20WWE.%20McMahon%20has%20denied%20the%20allegation%2C%20and%20the%20lawsuit%20is%20on%20hold%20while%20another%20court%20rules%20on%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20such%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20emailed%20statement%2C%20Trump-Vance%20transition%20spokesperson%20Liz%20Huston%20told%20BI%20that%20McMahon%20%26quot%3Bis%20ready%20to%20deliver%20on%20President%20Trump's%20agenda%20to%20restore%20America's%20education%20system%20and%20prepare%20our%20next%20generation%20for%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobinson%2C%20the%20Stanford%20researcher%2C%20said%20teachers%20would%20need%20much%20more%20funding%20to%20implement%20all%20the%20new%20bipartisan%20reading%20policies%20coming%20through%20states.%20Still%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20enough%20to%20simply%20shower%20schools%20with%20cash%20%E2%80%94%20smart%20policies%20are%20key.%20%E2%80%9CJust%20giving%20money%20without%20any%20guidelines%20isn't%20actually%20that%20helpful%20if%20you%20want%20it%20to%20be%20directed%20in%20a%20certain%20way%2C%E2%80%9D%20Robinson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20all%20of%20these%20moving%20parts%20have